item.title: Son accused of meat cleaver rampage
item.description: A man who allegedly threatened his neighbour with a meat cleaver after slapping his mother in the face during a domestic dispute in Sydney’s west has been hit with a number of charges.

item.title: New child sex charges for Scout leader
item.description: A former north shore Scout leader, who was arrested earlier this year over historic child sexual abuse allegations, has been slapped with nine new charges.

item.title: Police to clamp down on face masks
item.description: Victorians are being warned police “will not hesitate” to issue fines to people busted without face masks while out in public.

item.title: Second Melbourne prisoner becomes infected
item.description: A second prisoner at Melbourne’s Metropolitan Remand Centre has tested positive for coronavirus.

item.title: Workplace transmission ‘a real’ problem
item.description: A council in Melbourne’s west – plagued with more than 400 active cases of COVID-19 – will be targeting specific industries where workers are at risk of transmitting the wildly infectious disease.

item.title: Mick Gatto ‘in shock’ to be called murderer
item.description: Melbourne gangland figure Mick Gatto was “in a state of shock” to read an ABC article alleging he was a murderer, had threatened to kill lawyer Nicola Gobbo, and was one of Australia’s most violent criminals.

item.title: Boeing 747’s touching final finish
item.description: The Boeing 747’s farewell flight is forming the shape of the iconic Qantas kangaroo in the air.

item.title: $A to rise with improved Chinese economy
item.description: Forecast double digit growth in the Chinese economy has prompted Westpac’s chief economist Bill Evans to believe the Australian dollar will continue to rise for the remainder of the year.

item.title: Tsunami warning for parts of US
item.description: A 7.8-magnitude earthquake that struck off the Alaskan peninsula has triggered a tsunami warning for areas within 300km of the epicentre, including parts of the US.

item.title: Share market dips amid COVID rise
item.description: Local sharemarkets dipped on Wednesday as fresh fears of a second COVID-19 wave were realised following a jump in the number of Victorian cases.
